entities.name: ElizaOS
entities.description: An open-source framework for building and deploying AI agents, featuring architectural improvements, plugin ecosystem, and agent network economy concepts. Known for its v1.0.8 and v1.0.9 releases that introduced significant architectural enhancements.

entities.name: Twitter
entities.description: A social media platform enabling users to post and interact with messages known as 'tweets'. It is now owned by X Corp.

entities.name: Farcaster
entities.description: A decentralized social media protocol. It is being prepared as a backup communication platform for ElizaOS.

entities.name: Discord
entities.description: A voice over IP (VoIP) application and digital distribution platform for communities. It is used for real-time text, voice, and video communication.

entities.name: Spartan
entities.description: A product suite focused on DeFi and trading tools, developed as a separate stack from ElizaOS with a different architecture. It is nearing its first product release.

entities.name: GitHub
entities.description: A web-based platform for version control using Git. It provides hosting for software development version control using Git, as well as collaboration features.

entities.name: PostgreSQL
entities.description: An open-source relational database management system. It is known for its reliability, feature robustness, and performance.

entities.name: ai16z
entities.description: A company that focuses on getting products right and out the door, indicating it is in a growth phase. It is indicated to have sufficient funding (runway) but is not yet profitable.

entities.name: Ollama
entities.description: A tool that simplifies running large language models locally. It allows users to easily download and run models like Llama 2, Mistral, and others.

entities.name: AWS Bedrock
entities.description: A fully managed service from Amazon Web Services that offers a choice of high-performing foundation models (FMs) from leading AI companies via a single API.

entities.name: Gemini
entities.description: A family of multimodal large language models developed by Google. They are designed to understand and operate across text, code, images, audio, and video.

entities.name: Vertex AI
entities.description: A unified machine learning platform for Google Cloud. It enables users to build, train, and deploy ML models with integrated tools and services.

entities.name: Odilitime
entities.description: A community member or representative associated with ElizaOS, who has provided updates on profitability, product releases, and backup plans.

entities.name: boom
entities.description: A user who reported successfully automating the 'ainews' functionality within ElizaOS.

entities.name: cjft
entities.description: A contributor who expressed interest in developing token-based utility protocols, 'login with Eliza' services, and agent network economies.

entities.name: jin
entities.description: A contributor interested in designing agent trading competitions.

entities.name: orayo
entities.description: A contributor interested in creating a Gemini/VertexAI plugin for working with ML models for satellite images.

entities.name: Kenk
entities.description: A community member who pointed to a YouTube playlist showcasing projects built within ElizaOS.

entities.name: bitcryptowski.btc
